Two people have died after an aircraft they were in crashed at Vuria Hill in Taita Taveta County on Monday evening, authorities have confirmed.  The crashed aircraft is believed to be a C172 Caravan Reg No. 5Y CFE that was being operated by Flying Training Centre (FTC) and had two passengers on board.  The light fixed-wing aircraft took off from Wilson Airport in Nairobi on Monday at 1830hrs en route to Mombasa and is said to have crashed at around 1930hrs.  Vuria Hill is the highest peak in Taita Taveta County.   Chopper crashes after dropping Raila in Siaya  Marsabit plane crash  Boeing settles nearly all Lion Air 737 MAX crash claims: filing  Security chiefs injured in Meru police chopper crash The incident comes just a day after a chopper that had flown ODM leader Raila Odinga to a function crashed as it tried to lift off at Kudho Primary School in Gem, Siaya County  According to Raila’s spokesperson Dennis Onyango, the helicopter, Bell 407 registration 5Y-PSM was trying to create space for other choppers when it went down.  A video of the incident shows the chopper tilting before hitting the ground.  The accident left the pilot with slight injuries.  More details to follow.   Standard Group Sam Shollei; Launches KTN News Channel sensitization caravan  Sombre mood as injured KDF soldiers arrive in Nairobi from Somalia  Mandera Governor Ali Roba condemn alleged shooting of civilians by military personnel By Renson Mnyamwezi | 12 hours ago By Weldon Kipkemoi | 2 days ago By Obare Osinde | 2 days ago By Patrick Beja | 3 days ago Who is killing these men: Is it gangs or killer police squads?